CatDescriptText: He is an enlisted man in the U.S. Army serving in the General Headquarters Reserve, possibly in the Coast Artillery Branch.  His ribbon may represent an American Defense Medal.
TitMainTitle: Portrait of smiling man wearing belted U. S. Army uniform, dark tie, Coast Artillery insignia on lapel, Headquarters Army Ground Forces and Army Ground Forces Overhead patch on shoulder, and dark cap, posed in front of moire background, in Harris Studio
